    "where R in is the inner edge of the disc, and β = 3/4.",
    "The inner edge effects are commonly ignored (see Zdziarski et al. 2022, regarding the impact of disc truncation and wind), and the dependence T ∝ R -β is often kept as a first order generalisation of the thin-disc.",
    "For this model, the radius at which the temperature coincides with the rest wavelength of the observations (kT = h p c/λ rest) is:",
